WEBVTT

1
00:00:18.142 --> 00:00:22.127
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:22.691 --> 00:00:24.991
<i>[Episode 10]
[Longing Heart]</i>

3
00:00:27.016 --> 00:00:29.663
<i>[September 30, 2017]</i>

4
00:00:30.704 --> 00:00:31.999
<i>Mr. Kang.</i>

5
00:00:32.648 --> 00:00:33.975
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

6
00:00:34.670 --> 00:00:38.761
<i>And so, I'm going to change the future.</i>

7
00:00:38.761 --> 00:00:42.051
<i>["In Search of Lost Time"
by Marcel Proust]</i>

8
00:00:42.051 --> 00:00:46.225
<i>The things that happened to you
are still in the future for me.</i>

9
00:00:46.225 --> 00:00:47.832
<i>I won't...</i>

10
00:00:47.832 --> 00:00:51.977
<i>meet with Ji Soo
10 years from now, in Seoul.</i>

11
00:00:54.008 --> 00:00:55.548
<i>I will...</i>

12
00:00:56.006 --> 00:00:58.218
<i>only stop Ji Soo from
getting into that accident...</i>

13
00:00:58.218 --> 00:01:00.872
<i>and won't appear before her.</i>

14
00:01:01.801 --> 00:01:04.062
<i>[Shin Woo, there's something
I need to tell you.]</i>

15
00:01:04.062 --> 00:01:06.083
<i>[I'll wait for you tomorrow at
11 o' clock at Firefly Bridge.]</i>

16
00:01:06.083 --> 00:01:08.262
<i>And ten years later, on the day
of Mom's death anniversary</i>

17
00:01:08.262 --> 00:01:11.071
<i>I won't go to Firefly Bridge, either.</i>

18
00:01:25.374 --> 00:01:26.836
<i>If I do that,
the things that happened</i>

19
00:01:26.836 --> 00:01:30.709
<i>because you came back to 2007
won't ever have happened</i>

20
00:01:30.709 --> 00:01:35.020
<i>and everything that happened between
you and Ji Soo will never have happened.</i>

21
00:01:35.020 --> 00:01:36.725
<i>But I...</i>

22
00:01:37.193 --> 00:01:39.892
<i>hope that we part ways with Ji Soo
when we're 18 years old...</i>

23
00:01:39.892 --> 00:01:42.479
<i>and never meet her again.</i>

24
00:01:43.940 --> 00:01:46.199
<i>Meeting each other will only
cause both of us pain</i>

25
00:01:46.199 --> 00:01:49.500
<i>so there's no reason
to repeat all that.</i>

26
00:01:50.390 --> 00:01:52.319
<i>But, if I do this...</i>

27
00:01:52.943 --> 00:01:56.931
<i>Ji Soo may not remember you
in the future.</i>

28
00:01:56.931 --> 00:02:00.100
<i>Because the fact that
she met you as a teacher</i>

29
00:02:00.100 --> 00:02:03.037
<i>will never have happened.</i>

30
00:02:04.214 --> 00:02:06.977
Kang Shin Woo, you idiot!

31
00:03:35.350 --> 00:03:36.499
Oh!

32
00:03:36.499 --> 00:03:39.674
Isn't this the photo that
Geun Deok took of us last time?

33
00:03:39.674 --> 00:03:41.263
- Yeah.
- Huh?

34
00:03:41.263 --> 00:03:44.727
Geun Deok hasn't gotten
this photo printed yet, though.

35
00:03:44.727 --> 00:03:47.692
No, he already did
and gave me one first.

36
00:03:47.692 --> 00:03:49.507
A long time ago.

37
00:03:49.507 --> 00:03:52.268
Can't you give this to me, Mr. Kang?

38
00:03:52.268 --> 00:03:54.818
And you can ask Geun Deok
to print you another copy.

39
00:03:54.818 --> 00:03:56.202
Sure.

40
00:03:57.661 --> 00:04:00.679
Why does this photo look so old, though?

41
00:04:03.336 --> 00:04:06.620
<i>[The photo that Mr. Kang gave me]</i>

42
00:04:07.716 --> 00:04:09.977
<i>If I were your older brother</i>

43
00:04:09.977 --> 00:04:12.337
<i>I would've wanted to tell you that...</i>

44
00:04:12.337 --> 00:04:14.395
<i>it wasn't your fault.</i>

45
00:04:14.395 --> 00:04:17.215
And that nobody in this world
should ever feel guilty...

46
00:04:17.215 --> 00:04:19.171
for having survived.

47
00:04:19.852 --> 00:04:21.782
For someone...

48
00:04:22.313 --> 00:04:25.008
the mere fact that
you're in front of them right now...

49
00:04:25.830 --> 00:04:27.830
will be more than
good enough for them.

50
00:04:28.999 --> 00:04:30.835
It's okay.

51
00:04:31.775 --> 00:04:33.294
It's okay.

52
00:04:34.698 --> 00:04:36.674
This one memory...

53
00:04:37.446 --> 00:04:39.794
is the one that can't disappear.

54
00:04:40.537 --> 00:04:42.258
<i>Tell me...</i>

55
00:04:43.056 --> 00:04:44.955
<i>just one more time.</i>

56
00:04:46.167 --> 00:04:47.943
Just like you did back then.

57
00:04:48.787 --> 00:04:51.100
That it's okay.

58
00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:53.873
And that you're relieved...

59
00:04:53.873 --> 00:04:55.551
that I'm here now.

60
00:04:56.311 --> 00:04:59.003
And my being here right now
is more than good enough.

61
00:05:00.157 --> 00:05:01.941
Please tell me that...

62
00:05:02.643 --> 00:05:04.294
just one more time.

63
00:05:05.232 --> 00:05:08.612
So for her, she's probably
been waiting for the past ten years.

64
00:06:16.143 --> 00:06:18.475
It's okay if you forget everything.

65
00:06:20.099 --> 00:06:22.345
When we met again last time...

66
00:06:23.121 --> 00:06:28.400
you said that you don't remember
what happened in the past, right?

67
00:06:30.249 --> 00:06:32.436
You should truly live your life
like that now.

68
00:06:32.436 --> 00:06:34.691
Don't overexert yourself
and force yourself to not forget...

69
00:06:35.318 --> 00:06:37.652
and make yourself miserable by doing so.

70
00:06:41.612 --> 00:06:43.289
Even if...

71
00:06:44.650 --> 00:06:47.184
you end up forgetting everything...

72
00:06:48.366 --> 00:06:50.989
please remember this one thing.

73
00:06:51.965 --> 00:06:53.462
That...

74
00:06:54.004 --> 00:06:56.869
there is nobody who should
feel guilty for having survived.

75
00:06:58.595 --> 00:07:00.758
If I were to turn back time...

76
00:07:01.294 --> 00:07:03.676
and be in this very spot again...

77
00:07:05.001 --> 00:07:07.609
and I knew that
things would end like this...

78
00:07:09.304 --> 00:07:12.219
I would still have gone back to meet you
when you were eighteen years old.

79
00:07:13.609 --> 00:07:15.847
To tell you that...

80
00:07:19.323 --> 00:07:21.645
you didn't do anything wrong, Ji Soo.

81
00:07:24.044 --> 00:07:25.790
It wasn't your fault.

82
00:07:28.626 --> 00:07:30.640
I'm sorry, Shin Woo.

83
00:07:45.652 --> 00:07:48.445
What I couldn't tell you back then...

84
00:07:48.445 --> 00:07:50.765
<i>What's her name?</i>

85
00:07:50.765 --> 00:07:53.518
The name of your first love, I mean.

86
00:07:54.289 --> 00:07:56.138
<i>The name of my first love...</i>

87
00:07:57.323 --> 00:07:59.266
was Han Ji Soo.

88
00:08:00.220 --> 00:08:03.284
<i>Even if I give you a problem
that I know the answer to</i>

89
00:08:03.284 --> 00:08:06.948
<i>I can still hope that you'd
choose the wrong answer.</i>

90
00:08:09.042 --> 00:08:10.821
You were always...

91
00:08:12.436 --> 00:08:14.345
my answer.

92
00:08:17.249 --> 00:08:18.614
Thanks...

93
00:08:19.391 --> 00:08:21.046
for so many things...

94
00:08:22.950 --> 00:08:26.221
and for liking me
so many times.

95
00:10:17.319 --> 00:10:19.249
What's wrong, Big Sis?

96
00:10:20.817 --> 00:10:23.532
I got this back not too long ago...

97
00:10:24.330 --> 00:10:26.431
and they told me that
this was Mom's.

98
00:10:28.882 --> 00:10:31.739
I have to reorganize
all of her things...

99
00:10:32.354 --> 00:10:34.667
but I can't do it!

100
00:10:35.947 --> 00:10:37.947
Mom!

101
00:10:39.656 --> 00:10:42.009
Mom!

102
00:10:44.071 --> 00:10:45.971
Mom!

103
00:10:49.416 --> 00:10:51.236
I'll do it.

104
00:10:54.821 --> 00:10:56.747
I'll do it.

105
00:11:19.257 --> 00:11:22.229
Who got your bag
all dirty like this?

106
00:11:45.512 --> 00:11:47.694
This is my citizen ID.

107
00:11:49.685 --> 00:11:51.752
Why... did she have two of them?

108
00:12:04.233 --> 00:12:06.811
If this ticket is the one that
Ji Soo gave her...

109
00:12:10.105 --> 00:12:12.889
then, what's this?

110
00:12:38.245 --> 00:12:41.460
This is mine.

111
00:12:45.499 --> 00:12:47.048
But you know...

112
00:12:47.048 --> 00:12:49.144
on the day of Mom's accident...

113
00:12:49.604 --> 00:12:51.839
you didn't get a call
from Mom?

114
00:12:51.839 --> 00:12:53.272
A call?

115
00:12:53.272 --> 00:12:55.795
Mom didn't take her phone
with her that day, though.

116
00:12:55.795 --> 00:12:58.099
When I went to go
pick this up before

117
00:12:58.099 --> 00:13:02.534
I watched the CCTV footage because
I wanted to see her one last time.

118
00:13:03.245 --> 00:13:05.377
And Mom was on the phone.

119
00:13:05.377 --> 00:13:06.483
Really?

120
00:13:07.435 --> 00:13:09.547
I didn't get a call.

121
00:13:09.547 --> 00:13:11.845
Who was it, then?

122
00:13:21.591 --> 00:13:24.038
Huh?
What is this?

123
00:13:24.038 --> 00:13:26.547
When did I get this?

124
00:13:26.547 --> 00:13:28.893
Do they send spam through
voice mails now, too?

125
00:13:52.575 --> 00:13:54.143
<i>Shin Woo.</i>

126
00:13:55.343 --> 00:13:57.181
<i>It's Mom.</i>

127
00:13:57.181 --> 00:13:58.374
Mom.

128
00:14:00.632 --> 00:14:02.548
<i>And... Mr. Kang.</i>

129
00:14:04.622 --> 00:14:07.196
<i>Wait, no.
Not Mr. Kang.</i>

130
00:14:08.213 --> 00:14:10.292
<i>You're my Shin Woo,
aren't you?</i>

131
00:14:11.425 --> 00:14:15.836
You were quite sad because
I didn't recognize you, weren't you?

132
00:14:16.372 --> 00:14:18.013
<i>I have no idea...</i>

133
00:14:18.013 --> 00:14:21.412
how you came all the way
back here, after becoming an adult.

134
00:14:23.654 --> 00:14:26.207
I'm dumb, so no matter
how much I think about it

135
00:14:26.207 --> 00:14:27.970
I can't think of how
this could have happened.

136
00:14:28.899 --> 00:14:30.379
But...

137
00:14:32.782 --> 00:14:34.861
thinking about it now...

138
00:14:35.652 --> 00:14:38.183
this must have been...

139
00:14:38.705 --> 00:14:41.283
a gift to me, from the heavens.

140
00:14:42.694 --> 00:14:45.521
<i>A gift showing me that...</i>

141
00:14:46.133 --> 00:14:47.542
<i>my children grew up to
become fine adults</i>

142
00:14:47.542 --> 00:14:48.951
<i>even after I leave like this.</i>

143
00:14:51.028 --> 00:14:54.697
<i>In my eyes, Shin Woo,
you're still my baby.</i>

144
00:14:54.697 --> 00:15:00.388
<i>But this was a gift that is
making my heart rest at ease</i>

145
00:15:01.010 --> 00:15:02.697
<i>and allowing me go on in peace</i>

146
00:15:02.697 --> 00:15:05.816
<i>since you've grown up
to be such a fine adult.</i>

147
00:15:05.816 --> 00:15:07.498
So...

148
00:15:08.013 --> 00:15:09.763
right now...

149
00:15:09.763 --> 00:15:12.325
I'm not scared at all.

150
00:15:12.325 --> 00:15:14.808
And I'm not worried
in the slightest.

151
00:15:16.840 --> 00:15:19.569
Who could ever ask for
anything more?

152
00:15:20.114 --> 00:15:21.513
Right?

153
00:15:22.047 --> 00:15:23.503
<i>Also, Shin Woo.</i>

154
00:15:24.783 --> 00:15:27.456
<i>You remember the problem that
you and I discussed at my shop</i>

155
00:15:27.456 --> 00:15:31.005
<i>while we drank soju together?</i>

156
00:15:32.152 --> 00:15:34.961
<i>I think I found the answer already.</i>

157
00:15:35.845 --> 00:15:38.601
<i>You know, about why
the girl you like...</i>

158
00:15:39.215 --> 00:15:42.671
<i>was so cruel to you after seeing
you for the first time in ten years.</i>

159
00:15:42.671 --> 00:15:44.700
I think I must have

160
00:15:44.700 --> 00:15:47.969
wanted to send her
to you last time, too.

161
00:15:47.969 --> 00:15:50.254
Just like now.

162
00:15:50.254 --> 00:15:52.763
One ticket for the
2 o' clock ferry, please.

163
00:15:55.604 --> 00:15:57.504
There's no doubt about it.

164
00:15:57.504 --> 00:15:59.824
Mr. Kang is definitely my Shin Woo.

165
00:16:02.610 --> 00:16:05.242
He's my Shin Woo,
from 10 years in the future.

166
00:16:08.279 --> 00:16:10.176
Oh.

167
00:16:10.176 --> 00:16:13.113
And he didn't even get to call me "mom."

168
00:16:13.113 --> 00:16:18.345
He was in front of me this whole time,
and yet I didn't even realize that!

169
00:16:21.657 --> 00:16:23.257
She's...

170
00:16:23.257 --> 00:16:26.360
definitely the girl that
my Shin Woo likes.

171
00:16:26.921 --> 00:16:30.651
She's supposed to be meeting with my
Shin Woo now, so what's she doing here?

172
00:16:30.651 --> 00:16:33.643
Excuse me, Student!

173
00:16:33.643 --> 00:16:37.677
You're my Shin Woo's
classmate, right?

174
00:16:37.677 --> 00:16:42.038
By the way, did my Shin Woo
contact you last night, by any chance?

175
00:16:42.038 --> 00:16:43.691
Shin Woo?

176
00:16:45.658 --> 00:16:49.244
Oh, um... my phone is broken, so...

177
00:16:49.244 --> 00:16:50.356
Oh.

178
00:16:50.356 --> 00:16:53.532
By the way, where are
you headed, Ma'am?

179
00:16:53.532 --> 00:16:55.249
Oh, me?

180
00:16:55.249 --> 00:16:58.128
I, um...

181
00:16:58.128 --> 00:17:01.505
I'm on my way to visit someone
since they said that they were sick.

182
00:17:01.505 --> 00:17:03.811
But they said that all the
tickets for the ferry are sold out.

183
00:17:03.811 --> 00:17:05.555
Oh, and I really have to go, too!

184
00:17:05.555 --> 00:17:07.580
How terrible.
What should I do?

185
00:17:07.580 --> 00:17:10.230
Would you like to take my ticket, then?

186
00:17:10.230 --> 00:17:12.208
Really?
Can I take it?

187
00:17:12.208 --> 00:17:14.574
I have no intention of leaving
to study abroad, anyway.

188
00:17:14.574 --> 00:17:16.072
I don't need to go.

189
00:17:16.072 --> 00:17:17.515
Here.

190
00:17:18.209 --> 00:17:19.756
All right, thanks!

191
00:17:19.756 --> 00:17:21.015
Then...

192
00:17:21.639 --> 00:17:22.717
Um...

193
00:17:22.717 --> 00:17:25.589
um, here.

194
00:17:25.589 --> 00:17:27.763
I'll give you this
in exchange.

195
00:17:28.771 --> 00:17:31.751
Oh, it's so pretty on you
and fits perfectly!

196
00:17:31.751 --> 00:17:34.304
This is too generous of a gift for me
to accept in exchange for a ticket.

197
00:17:34.304 --> 00:17:37.340
Then, can you do me a favor?

198
00:17:37.340 --> 00:17:41.694
Can you get your cellphone fixed
as soon as you leave this place?

199
00:17:41.694 --> 00:17:43.428
My... phone?

200
00:17:43.428 --> 00:17:44.755
Yeah.

201
00:17:44.755 --> 00:17:48.650
Oh, it's time for my ferry
so I'll be leaving now.

202
00:17:48.650 --> 00:17:51.386
All right.
Goodbye.

203
00:17:52.111 --> 00:17:54.167
<i>So, if you meet her again...</i>

204
00:17:54.167 --> 00:17:56.163
<i>be sure to tell her that
it wasn't bad luck that you two met again</i>

205
00:17:56.163 --> 00:17:58.245
<i>but rather, that it was fate.</i>

206
00:17:58.245 --> 00:17:59.841
Tell her that your mom...

207
00:18:00.324 --> 00:18:02.377
held your hand tight...

208
00:18:02.377 --> 00:18:05.330
and created this opportunity
for you two to be together.

209
00:18:05.330 --> 00:18:07.259
<i>My Shin Hee...</i>

210
00:18:07.859 --> 00:18:09.279
<i>and my Shin Woo.</i>

211
00:18:09.279 --> 00:18:11.475
<i>The thing about happiness is that
you need to hold onto it tightly</i>

212
00:18:11.475 --> 00:18:14.538
<i>with your own hands for you
to keep it by your side.</i>

213
00:18:14.538 --> 00:18:16.899
<i>So don't let it slip through
your fingers...</i>

214
00:18:17.548 --> 00:18:21.376
<i>so you have to hold onto it tightly
and live happily, okay?</i>

215
00:18:21.376 --> 00:18:23.554
As much as...

216
00:18:23.554 --> 00:18:25.843
my love for you two.

217
00:18:50.274 --> 00:18:52.818
I have to tell this to Ji Soo.

218
00:18:56.717 --> 00:18:59.686
But I don't even know
where Ji Soo is now.

219
00:19:04.193 --> 00:19:06.183
Yeah, So Ra.

220
00:19:06.183 --> 00:19:08.780
What time did you say Ji Soo's
flight was today, again?

221
00:19:18.767 --> 00:19:21.545
<i>I told you that I'd
tell you my name, right?</i>

222
00:19:21.545 --> 00:19:25.155
<i>My name is Kang Shin Woo.</i>

223
00:19:25.155 --> 00:19:26.809
My first love's name...

224
00:19:26.809 --> 00:19:28.765
was Han Ji Soo.

225
00:19:28.765 --> 00:19:30.968
What's her name?

226
00:19:30.968 --> 00:19:32.650
Your first love's name, I mean.

227
00:19:32.650 --> 00:19:35.936
That's something that I really
can't tell you right now.

228
00:19:35.936 --> 00:19:37.372
Why not?

229
00:19:37.372 --> 00:19:38.716
Later.

230
00:19:38.716 --> 00:19:40.734
I'll tell you later.

231
00:19:40.734 --> 00:19:42.511
You were always...

232
00:19:43.709 --> 00:19:45.681
my answer.

233
00:19:50.414 --> 00:19:51.917
What's the matter?

234
00:19:54.462 --> 00:19:56.143
Senior.

235
00:19:56.143 --> 00:19:57.855
If, by any chance,
you thought that...

236
00:19:57.855 --> 00:20:01.902
a person that you met in the past
and a person you met in the present

237
00:20:01.902 --> 00:20:05.044
were two different people...

238
00:20:05.044 --> 00:20:09.001
but it turned out that
they were the same person...

239
00:20:09.738 --> 00:20:12.431
how could something
like that be possible?

240
00:20:12.431 --> 00:20:13.779
Time travel?

241
00:20:13.779 --> 00:20:16.015
But that makes no sense.

242
00:20:16.015 --> 00:20:19.219
I guess they must have been determined
enough to make the impossible possible.

243
00:20:19.921 --> 00:20:21.949
I'm just kidding.

244
00:20:21.949 --> 00:20:24.824
Why, did you see a plot like that
in a book, or something?

245
00:20:25.642 --> 00:20:27.009
Senior.

246
00:20:27.009 --> 00:20:31.279
I think I'll have to meet with
someone before I go.

247
00:20:33.248 --> 00:20:35.306
Stop it, Ji Soo.

248
00:20:35.715 --> 00:20:36.970
I...

249
00:20:37.564 --> 00:20:39.905
always thought
that it was strange that

250
00:20:39.905 --> 00:20:43.850
you hate talking about
your high school days...

251
00:20:43.860 --> 00:20:46.407
and yet you treasure
that photo so much.

