00:25:17.257 --> 00:25:18.649
<i>Did you meet with Ji Soo?</i>

314
00:25:18.649 --> 00:25:20.093
No.

315
00:25:21.929 --> 00:25:23.644
I think that I was...

316
00:25:24.206 --> 00:25:25.923
too late again.

317
00:25:38.528 --> 00:25:43.113
<i>[Garam High School]</i>

318
00:26:25.353 --> 00:26:28.327
<i>[Class 2-3]
[Homeroom Teacher: Kang Shin Woo]</i>

319
00:27:00.991 --> 00:27:02.680
Shin Woo.

320
00:27:05.912 --> 00:27:07.922
And... Mr. Kang.

321
00:27:11.063 --> 00:27:12.679
And...

322
00:27:13.322 --> 00:27:15.514
that little kid, too.

323
00:27:16.151 --> 00:27:18.421
all of those people
were you?

324
00:27:21.334 --> 00:27:23.919
All those people I liked...

325
00:27:24.461 --> 00:27:26.607
were all really you?

326
00:27:32.894 --> 00:27:34.222
For me...

327
00:27:34.797 --> 00:27:36.501
it was always you.

328
00:27:37.636 --> 00:27:39.894
Even though I went back in time...

329
00:27:40.527 --> 00:27:42.828
and no matter
what time I lived in...

330
00:27:44.773 --> 00:27:46.767
my answer was always...

331
00:27:47.943 --> 00:27:49.978
only you.

332
00:27:54.226 --> 00:27:57.134
I thought that I'd lost you again.

333
00:27:57.697 --> 00:27:59.282
How could I go...

334
00:27:59.884 --> 00:28:01.634
when now, I finally know...

335
00:28:02.160 --> 00:28:04.671
what she meant by that?

336
00:28:13.466 --> 00:28:15.438
Your mother's...

337
00:28:17.241 --> 00:28:19.241
final request, I mean.

338
00:28:21.027 --> 00:28:24.459
Oh yeah, I have one more
favor to ask of you.

339
00:28:24.459 --> 00:28:26.410
Yes, go ahead.

340
00:28:28.315 --> 00:28:32.653
Please take good care
of my sons.

341
00:28:32.653 --> 00:28:34.244
Your... sons?

342
00:28:34.244 --> 00:28:35.726
Yeah.

343
00:28:36.646 --> 00:28:38.642
My sons.

344
00:28:39.524 --> 00:28:40.966
Um...

345
00:28:40.966 --> 00:28:45.985
if my silly Shin Woo isn't able
to say anything to you...

346
00:28:45.985 --> 00:28:47.854
then...

347
00:28:47.854 --> 00:28:52.064
when you meet him later,
like, much later...

348
00:28:52.064 --> 00:28:54.367
don't say that you hate him.

349
00:28:54.367 --> 00:28:56.280
Instead, be nice to him.

350
00:28:56.280 --> 00:28:58.219
Do it for me.

351
00:28:58.219 --> 00:29:02.524
My Shin Woo will have grown up to
be a kind, upstanding young man.

352
00:29:02.524 --> 00:29:04.682
I can guarantee you that.

353
00:29:07.276 --> 00:29:10.432
This fits you so well, as if
it was meant to be yours, huh?

354
00:29:10.432 --> 00:29:14.566
I really hope that you'll keep this
on your finger for a long, long time.

355
00:29:29.526 --> 00:29:31.642
I'll give this back to you.

356
00:29:34.197 --> 00:29:36.430
I'm sure that my mom...

357
00:29:37.029 --> 00:29:39.411
would definitely want you
to have this.

358
00:29:52.439 --> 00:29:54.113
To tell you the truth...

359
00:29:54.683 --> 00:29:56.638
I missed you.

360
00:29:58.097 --> 00:29:59.930
Quite a lot.

361
00:30:08.389 --> 00:30:11.065
All I can say to you...

362
00:30:11.927 --> 00:30:15.409
is that I'm sorry.

363
00:30:18.081 --> 00:30:20.086
And after that would be...

364
00:30:20.776 --> 00:30:23.080
"I want to see you."

365
00:30:23.080 --> 00:30:25.205
And that I missed you.

366
00:30:26.860 --> 00:30:29.821
And then, I think of other
things that I want to say...

367
00:30:31.155 --> 00:30:33.122
which makes me feel bad.

368
00:30:40.142 --> 00:30:41.323
And then...

369
00:30:41.876 --> 00:30:43.834
on days that I start thinking

370
00:30:44.399 --> 00:30:49.434
that it should've been me
who got on that ferry...

371
00:30:52.427 --> 00:30:55.981
I missed Mr. Kang quite a lot.

372
00:30:59.130 --> 00:31:01.485
And I didn't even know
that he was actually you.

373
00:31:03.653 --> 00:31:07.249
So I guess that,
for the past ten years...

374
00:31:07.942 --> 00:31:11.834
I was only ever thinking about you.

375
00:31:13.671 --> 00:31:15.168
What about you?

376
00:31:15.168 --> 00:31:17.305
My memories...

377
00:31:17.923 --> 00:31:21.394
are all a mess, in terms of chronological
order and space-time.

378
00:31:22.034 --> 00:31:24.702
<i>My memories of the first
2007 that I lived through</i>

379
00:31:24.702 --> 00:31:26.900
<i>where we parted ways
without knowing anything.</i>

380
00:31:27.721 --> 00:31:32.448
<i>And my memories as a 28-year-old
when I went back to 2007.</i>

381
00:31:33.210 --> 00:31:36.536
<i>And my memories of coming
to 2017, as an 18-year-old.</i>

382
00:31:37.171 --> 00:31:39.899
<i>And my memories of
returning to 2007</i>

383
00:31:39.899 --> 00:31:42.766
and having lived my life
up until now.

384
00:31:45.874 --> 00:31:49.653
All of those things are
things that I experienced.

385
00:31:52.138 --> 00:31:55.285
And so, all of those
memories are mine.

386
00:31:56.302 --> 00:32:00.412
Sometimes, I get confused
and get things mixed up.

387
00:32:01.180 --> 00:32:03.928
But, one thing is for sure.

388
00:32:11.441 --> 00:32:14.020
And that's the fact that...

389
00:32:14.584 --> 00:32:16.831
I met you every single time...

390
00:32:17.415 --> 00:32:19.170
and liked you...

391
00:32:20.174 --> 00:32:21.978
and so...

392
00:32:22.593 --> 00:32:24.640
I was always waiting for you.

393
00:32:52.392 --> 00:32:54.420
<i>Fate seemed cruel and powerful</i>

394
00:32:54.420 --> 00:32:56.690
<i>and impossible to change,
no matter what I did</i>

395
00:32:56.690 --> 00:32:59.093
<i>even when I re-lived my life.</i>

396
00:32:59.900 --> 00:33:02.194
<i>But now I know</i>

397
00:33:02.194 --> 00:33:04.370
<i>that the truly powerful thing...</i>

398
00:33:04.370 --> 00:33:06.806
<i>hadn't been fate.</i>

399
00:33:09.276 --> 00:33:11.456
<i>Even when I re-lived my life...</i>

400
00:33:12.061 --> 00:33:14.504
<i>you were the one
that I liked each time.</i>

401
00:33:17.456 --> 00:33:20.603
<i>And you liked me back
each and every time.</i>

402
00:33:22.086 --> 00:33:23.669
<i>And...</i>

403
00:33:32.332 --> 00:33:33.850
<i>my mom.</i>

404
00:33:40.394 --> 00:33:42.982
<i>Our miraculous present</i>

405
00:33:42.982 --> 00:33:45.468
<i>which was made possible through
the love of all of these people.</i>

406
00:33:45.468 --> 00:33:47.728
There isn't anything
that you want?

407
00:33:48.296 --> 00:33:49.497
Yeah.

408
00:33:49.497 --> 00:33:51.880
I only have things
that I want to give to you.

409
00:33:55.071 --> 00:33:56.793
Exactly.

410
00:33:56.793 --> 00:33:59.266
I'm only ever
receiving things from you.

411
00:33:59.975 --> 00:34:03.223
Well, then... a birthday present.

412
00:34:04.614 --> 00:34:06.727
Every day, until I become
100 years old.

413
00:34:10.538 --> 00:34:14.857
Coming here makes me
want to see Deok Goo.

414
00:34:14.857 --> 00:34:16.535
Deok Goo?

415
00:34:17.863 --> 00:34:20.870
It almost feels like I'm hearing you say
your ex-boyfriend's name.

416
00:34:25.096 --> 00:34:28.658
I kind of want to see that punk, too.

417
00:34:37.939 --> 00:34:41.667
<i>In his own time,
that punk is...</i>

418
00:34:43.180 --> 00:34:46.848
<i>He's walking forward cautiously,
step by step</i>

419
00:34:46.848 --> 00:34:50.440
<i>and following in my footsteps.</i>

420
00:35:01.946 --> 00:35:03.477
<i>Mr. Kang.</i>

421
00:35:03.477 --> 00:35:07.346
<i>You're definitely with
Ji Soo right now, right?</i>

422
00:35:07.346 --> 00:35:10.672
<i>Ji Soo is happy, right?</i>

423
00:35:11.672 --> 00:35:13.904
<i>I'll believe that.</i>

424
00:35:13.904 --> 00:35:18.303
<i>And so, I've decided to bet
everything I have on that future.</i>

425
00:35:18.303 --> 00:35:24.232
<i>Because I can't have your and Ji Soo's
present change because of me.</i>

426
00:35:33.310 --> 00:35:35.163
Give that here.

427
00:35:38.201 --> 00:35:39.504
I'm going to this university.

428
00:35:39.504 --> 00:35:41.567
Hankook University.
Math Education major.

429
00:35:41.567 --> 00:35:43.571
You're only a second year
in high school.

430
00:35:43.571 --> 00:35:45.502
And yet, you're thinking about re-taking
your college entrance exams already?

431
00:35:45.502 --> 00:35:47.580
I'm going to get in when I'm
in my third year, okay?

432
00:35:50.223 --> 00:35:51.388
How, exactly?

433
00:35:51.388 --> 00:35:53.094
Are you planning to be reborn?

434
00:35:53.779 --> 00:35:55.301
Gosh, I can't believe you.

