00:36:03.230 --> 00:36:05.745
And you want to get your
teacher certification in 2015?

439
00:36:09.502 --> 00:36:11.794
I have to live like this,
no matter what.

440
00:36:11.794 --> 00:36:13.841
So that nothing changes.

441
00:36:13.841 --> 00:36:15.027
Huh?

442
00:36:15.950 --> 00:36:17.464
Oh yeah.

443
00:36:17.464 --> 00:36:20.797
Do you know which division of the
military my old homeroom teacher joined?

444
00:36:20.797 --> 00:36:22.312
The Marines.

445
00:36:23.029 --> 00:36:26.669
He said that he went somewhere difficult
because of his first love, or whatever.

446
00:36:26.669 --> 00:36:27.933
Ugh.

447
00:36:28.614 --> 00:36:30.906
<i>[Marines]</i>

448
00:36:30.906 --> 00:36:32.078
Ugh, seriously!

449
00:36:32.078 --> 00:36:33.756
I just can't bring myself to like him.

450
00:36:35.350 --> 00:36:36.564
Just study.

451
00:36:43.314 --> 00:36:45.446
<i>I pray every day...</i>

452
00:36:46.078 --> 00:36:48.694
<i>for nothing more,
and nothing less.</i>

453
00:36:48.694 --> 00:36:50.439
<i>Just that...</i>

454
00:36:51.015 --> 00:36:52.812
<i>we'll always be like this.</i>

455
00:36:53.491 --> 00:36:56.165
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

456
00:36:56.165 --> 00:36:59.714
By the side of my friends,
who've suddenly discovered their dreams.

457
00:37:01.681 --> 00:37:03.643
Seriously, congrats,
Min Seok!

458
00:37:03.643 --> 00:37:06.464
Yeah, congrats. I heard your
webtoon is being made into a movie.

459
00:37:06.464 --> 00:37:07.785
Thank you.

460
00:37:07.785 --> 00:37:10.549
I told you that I have a great eye.

461
00:37:10.575 --> 00:37:13.672
Who was the one who threatened
him with divorce, again?

462
00:37:14.218 --> 00:37:15.290
Ow!

463
00:37:15.290 --> 00:37:16.913
All that there's left now is for you to
make tons of money

464
00:37:16.913 --> 00:37:18.701
and have So Ra open her own salon.

465
00:37:18.701 --> 00:37:21.259
Yeah. I'll get her a salon, and we'll
have to have another child, too.

466
00:37:21.259 --> 00:37:23.178
Are you going to keep on
spouting nonsense?

467
00:37:23.178 --> 00:37:24.488
Well, I'm going to be the one
raising them, anyway!

468
00:37:24.488 --> 00:37:27.468
You can talk when you can be the one
to give birth to the kid too, then.

469
00:37:27.468 --> 00:37:29.192
- No!
- Why, you...

470
00:37:30.448 --> 00:37:34.254
But still, it must be nice that you guys
had kids early and raised them already.

471
00:37:35.051 --> 00:37:36.299
Yes, well...

472
00:37:36.299 --> 00:37:37.752
But um, Ms. Baek.

473
00:37:37.752 --> 00:37:40.681
Thank you so much for
congratulating us, but...

474
00:37:40.681 --> 00:37:44.946
why... are you here?

475
00:37:45.625 --> 00:37:46.710
Hey!

476
00:37:46.710 --> 00:37:48.315
Well, the thing is...

477
00:37:49.078 --> 00:37:50.314
Oh!

478
00:37:50.314 --> 00:37:52.763
